@node "Requirements" "System Requirements"

   PPC hardware with a fast CPU of @{b}1GHZ@{ub} to plays videoformat of high compression level
 or with a big screen size.  To fast CPU more big the video and the best to decompress
 the video codec as mp4, flv and DivX.


  - The Hollywood pluggins:
        * OggTheora: ogg video.
        * AVCodec1-1: Videoformats.
        * MovieSetter: Movie Setter movies.
        * Scalable Vector Graphics: vectorgraphcis and xmlparser.
    Availables:
        http://www.hollywood-mal.com


    Others:
        * Datatypes.
        * WarpDTtypes. http://www.futaura.co.uk/
@endnode


@node "Install" "Installation"
  Copy V.A.M.P. where you want in your hard disk, USB stick, etc.
@endnode


@node "Play" "Playing"
  The window has the buttons to:

    - "Load"  multimedia file, it isn't a multimedia file a requester is opens to tell you.

    - "Play" multimedia file.

    - "Pause" multimedia file.

    - "Stop" the multimedia file.

    - "Speaker" mute the sound file, unmute clicking again on Sound volume bar.

    - "Sound volume bar" to change the volume video.

    - "Playing status multimedia file" the video position and rewind/forward.


    Others important things:

    - You can move the player in the Workbench window gettin the top player window.

    - You can change the player size window getting from the right bottom.


    And the keyboard hotkeys:

    - ESC: Exit the program.

    - I-i: Information about the multimedia file.

    - A-a: About the program version, author.

    - SPACE: Pause the video.


@endnode


@node "Limit" "Limitations"
   1. When you use V.A.M.P. and other player of video, sound or music, for limitations
      of programming  language it uses the  same sound channel that them,  crashed the
      VAMP program.

   2. When you play a video with V.A.M.P. and other videoplayer or viceversa the system
      freezes or crashes because the CPU doesn't work uncompressing two videos.

   3. Some video formats aren't supported, and other limitations of speed  with videos
      with a big size or a codec very compressed.

   4. Some pictures and videos with big screen sizes.

@endnode


